Paul Greenhalgh, &quot;Modernism in Design (Reaktion Books - Critical Views)&quot;
Reaktion Books | 1997-07-01 | ISBN: 0948462116 | 248 pages | PDF | 16 MB

This book reasserts the meaning of Modernism as a historical phenomenon. The essays consider design in its widest sense and look at Modernism's fortunes in the USA, Britain and Germany amongst other countries and range in subject matter from world fairs and domestic objects to American West Coast architecture and French and Italian furniture.
